Do you think there is possibly someone
around you who is related to Ma Dae Young?

251
00:23:35,160 --> 00:23:36,760
Joon Jae.

252
00:23:43,270 --> 00:23:48,010
I was really drunk last time. You must have
been startled after receiving the call.

253
00:23:48,010 --> 00:23:50,880
Saying that you will protect your mother,

254
00:23:50,880 --> 00:23:53,550
so protect my father, was also
something you said because you were drunk?

255
00:23:53,550 --> 00:23:58,380
Oh, did I say that? I must have been really drunk.

256
00:23:59,120 --> 00:24:02,250
What about father's health being bad?

257
00:24:02,250 --> 00:24:04,120
Oh, he is better now.

258
00:24:04,120 --> 00:24:11,600
Hey, our father gave all the work to
me and went on a trip with his friends.

259
00:24:15,700 --> 00:24:21,710
Also, you will know this sooner or later...

260
00:24:22,370 --> 00:24:25,110
Father got his will notarized.

261
00:24:25,110 --> 00:24:30,520
He left almost all his assets to me and Mother.

262
00:24:30,520 --> 00:24:34,820
I told him to reconsider several times.

263
00:24:34,820 --> 00:24:39,460
After meeting you the last time,
he must have been heartbroken.

264
00:24:41,430 --> 00:24:44,360
Were you always such a friendly guy?

265
00:24:45,600 --> 00:24:49,900
I will hate my father on my own.

266
00:24:49,900 --> 00:24:53,310
You don't need to encourage me to hate him.

267
00:24:54,510 --> 00:24:59,610
If you keep doing this, it looks
like you have some ulterior motive.

268
00:25:03,980 --> 00:25:05,720
What about Cheong?

269
00:25:07,490 --> 00:25:08,820
Is she well?

270
00:25:08,820 --> 00:25:11,260
Why would you ask that?

271
00:25:11,260 --> 00:25:16,630
That's right. I think of her time to time.
I wonder if she is doing well.

272
00:25:16,630 --> 00:25:18,360
Send my greetings to her.

273
00:25:18,360 --> 00:25:20,270
Why should I?

274
00:25:25,740 --> 00:25:27,610
Forget it, if you don't want to.

275
00:25:38,220 --> 00:25:39,890
Oh, no. I don't know what to do!

276
00:25:44,960 --> 00:25:54,600
Joon Jae, it turns out that the
ajumoni at our house is your moth—

277
00:26:00,810 --> 00:26:03,380
What brings you in here?

278
00:26:03,380 --> 00:26:09,680
I heard you are sick. You couldn't even
go to work. Try eating some porridge.

279
00:26:09,680 --> 00:26:14,290
Oh, I got sick uselessly to make you do extra work.

280
00:26:14,290 --> 00:26:16,660
What shall I do?

281
00:26:16,660 --> 00:26:20,530
Oh, it's okay. Call me after you
are done so I can take it away.

282
00:26:20,530 --> 00:26:26,200
Omo! It's not like I don't have hands
or feet. Who would I dare to call?

283
00:26:26,200 --> 00:26:31,040
After I'm done, I will clean it up myself.
Please do not mind me at all.

284
00:26:31,040 --> 00:26:33,610
Alright, then.

285
00:26:36,680 --> 00:26:39,380
Why are you doing this, Ji Young's aunt?!

286
00:26:39,380 --> 00:26:42,980
I wanted to do this just once.

287
00:26:45,080 --> 00:26:49,760
I am sorry, but I feel a bit uncomfortable.

288
00:26:51,620 --> 00:26:54,190
I am sorry.

289
00:27:03,300 --> 00:27:07,310
- Madam, Ji Young's aunt seems very sick.
- Really?

290
00:27:07,340 --> 00:27:10,440
You know, she is not her normal self.
She's a bit strange.

291
00:27:10,440 --> 00:27:13,810
She was never normal anyway.

292
00:27:14,710 --> 00:27:15,750
The number you have called—

293
00:27:15,750 --> 00:27:19,620
Ah, Kang Seo Hee, this woman!
She is ignoring my call again!

294
00:27:19,620 --> 00:27:22,550
Ha! Seriously!

295
00:27:26,430 --> 00:27:28,560
Excuse me.

296
00:27:28,560 --> 00:27:29,630
Yes?

297
00:27:29,630 --> 00:27:31,900
Their son...

298
00:27:31,900 --> 00:27:35,470
Son? Chairman Heo's real son?

299
00:27:35,470 --> 00:27:38,740
Yes, do you know something about that son?

300
00:27:38,740 --> 00:27:41,540
Why are you curious about that, Ajumma?

301
00:27:42,640 --> 00:27:44,240
Just because...

302
00:27:44,240 --> 00:27:48,410
The son who's taking care of
all of CEO Heo's business is

303
00:27:48,410 --> 00:27:51,120
the son who was brought in by Kang Seo Hee.

304
00:27:51,120 --> 00:27:56,520
His biological son ran out of the house
ten years ago, and no one knows where he is.

305
00:27:56,520 --> 00:27:59,260
He ran out of the house?

306
00:27:59,260 --> 00:28:00,630
He didn't go to study overseas?

307
00:28:00,630 --> 00:28:07,130
Study overseas? I don't think so. I clearly heard
that he ran away when he was in high school.

308
00:28:07,130 --> 00:28:11,540
At that rate, if Kang Seo Hee's
son receives all the inheritance,

309
00:28:11,540 --> 00:28:14,910
only the strangers will be
benefiting from his household.

310
00:28:14,910 --> 00:28:17,610
Chairman Heo is not that bright.

311
00:28:17,610 --> 00:28:19,710
What kind of father is he?

312
00:28:19,710 --> 00:28:24,680
Why would he abandon his own son and
dedicate himself to someone else's son?

313
00:28:24,680 --> 00:28:28,750
Ah, seriously. No matter how much he is
head over heels over a woman, how could he?

314
00:28:36,230 --> 00:28:39,970
Ajumma, what's the matter?

315
00:28:39,970 --> 00:28:42,270
Excuse me. I need to go somewhere.

316
00:28:42,270 --> 00:28:47,710
But it's time for children to come back from
school. You need to prepare their snack.

317
00:28:48,770 --> 00:28:52,140
Please go, Mother-jumoni.

318
00:28:52,140 --> 00:28:54,750
I will take care of the children, Unni.

319
00:28:54,750 --> 00:29:00,020
I will prepare kids' snacks and
take them to after school academies.

320
00:29:01,690 --> 00:29:06,320
That ajumma! Is she just doing whatever
she wants because she is quitting or what?!

321
00:29:06,320 --> 00:29:08,530
Unni, please!

322
00:29:09,160 --> 00:29:11,900
She must have something to take care of.

323
00:29:11,900 --> 00:29:15,630
Also, how can you call her "ajumma," seriously?!

324
00:29:15,630 --> 00:29:19,170
I should call an ajumma, ajumma.
What else should I call her then?

325
00:29:19,170 --> 00:29:22,670
Who calls household helpers ajumma these days?

326
00:29:22,670 --> 00:29:25,040
The going trend is, "Mother/Mother-in-Law."

327
00:29:25,040 --> 00:29:25,790
Auntie,

328
00:29:25,790 --> 00:29:30,520
the age different between that ajumma and
I is not that great for me to call her "Mother."

329
00:29:30,520 --> 00:29:33,550
- What's with "Mother"?  - "Mother" is nothing more than

330
00:29:33,550 --> 00:29:38,190
sharing the same meal and
sleeping under the same roof.

331
00:29:38,190 --> 00:29:42,330
She prepares my meals and even does my laundry.

332
00:29:43,900 --> 00:29:48,130
I've even let Mother wash my underwear!

333
00:29:48,130 --> 00:29:50,640
Oh, I'm going nuts!

334
00:30:27,070 --> 00:30:30,780
Chi Hyeon, go in first. Greet your father well.

335
00:30:30,780 --> 00:30:32,340
Yes.

336
00:30:34,180 --> 00:30:39,380
Are you leaving now? I came late
on purpose, to come after you left.

337
00:30:39,380 --> 00:30:41,050
Are you happy?

338
00:30:41,050 --> 00:30:46,260
I'm sorry. Even though you may not
believe me, I didn't do it on purpose.

339
00:30:46,260 --> 00:30:53,000
Oh, really? I believe you. I need to believe it.

340
00:30:53,000 --> 00:30:59,770
You have to raise my Joon Jae now. I am hoping
that you are a good person more than anyone else.

341
00:30:59,770 --> 00:31:03,720
That's right. I'm sure my husband told you already,

342
00:31:03,720 --> 00:31:07,210
but please don't show up until our
Joon Jae becomes an adult.

343
00:31:07,210 --> 00:31:10,320
That way he can grow
accustomed to the new family.

344
00:31:12,920 --> 00:31:18,390
Don't worry. I will raise and
love him more than my own son.

345
00:31:30,840 --> 00:31:34,170
- Who? - She says she is Mo Yoo Ran.

346
00:31:35,670 --> 00:31:38,780
How dare she come here?

347
00:31:39,680 --> 00:31:41,650
Open it.

348
00:31:55,690 --> 00:32:02,730
Oh, my! How long has it been?

349
00:32:02,730 --> 00:32:04,640
Have a seat.

350
00:32:04,640 --> 00:32:06,840
What would you like to drink?

351
00:32:08,110 --> 00:32:11,740
Ajumma, please excuse us for a while.

352
00:32:15,280 --> 00:32:17,880
Are you going to stand up and talk? Have a seat.

353
00:32:17,880 --> 00:32:20,290
Where is my Joon Jae?

354
00:32:21,490 --> 00:32:23,960
Where is he?

355
00:32:23,990 --> 00:32:28,160
- Why are you asking me about
your son? He is your son.  - What?

356
00:32:28,160 --> 00:32:31,290
It looks like you came knowing that
your son isn't in our house.

357
00:32:31,290 --> 00:32:34,500
Why are you asking me about him?

358
00:32:34,500 --> 00:32:39,340
I've never kicked him out. He went out on his own.

359
00:32:39,340 --> 00:32:44,210
And my husband didn't really try to look
for him, so that's why it came to this.

360
00:32:44,210 --> 00:32:47,580
Oh, this is what it's all about?

361
00:32:47,580 --> 00:32:52,980
I thought you two were keeping in
touch, but I guess not.

362
00:32:52,980 --> 00:32:55,950
You said you'd raise him well.

363
00:32:56,720 --> 00:33:00,130
I was planning to, but what can I do since he left?

364
00:33:00,130 --> 00:33:03,660
Is this why you didn't allow us to meet?

365
00:33:03,660 --> 00:33:10,940
To make my son yours, my husband yours,
and my position yours. Is that why?

366
00:33:13,240 --> 00:33:15,470
You are really funny.

367
00:33:15,470 --> 00:33:19,980
Hey! Don't pretend to be nice.

368
00:33:19,980 --> 00:33:22,410
You just gave up.

369
00:33:22,410 --> 00:33:27,890
If it were me, I would not have given up.
I would not have run away, leaving my son.

370
00:33:27,890 --> 00:33:32,420
Just because I told you not to meet,
you really don't meet him? Are you stupid?

371
00:33:32,420 --> 00:33:33,430
What?

372
00:33:33,430 --> 00:33:37,830
If you aren't going to have some tea,
can you leave now? I'm really tired.

373
00:33:37,830 --> 00:33:39,870
Kang Ji Yeon!

374
00:33:44,870 --> 00:33:48,940
My name is Kang Seo Hee.

375
00:33:48,940 --> 00:33:52,610
No, your name is Kang Ji Yeon.

376
00:33:52,610 --> 00:33:58,050
My son. I will definitely find him and
bring him back to where he belongs.

377
00:33:58,050 --> 00:34:03,190
You, too. I will take you back
to your original position.

378
00:34:20,040 --> 00:34:22,070
Yes, it's me.

379
00:34:36,460 --> 00:34:37,220
Miss Cheong.

380
00:34:37,220 --> 00:34:39,830
All right! All right!

381
00:34:42,460 --> 00:34:44,000
You should watch out for cars.

382
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:49,500
- Pay attention to oncoming cars. He
said not to be absent minded.  - Who did?

383
00:34:49,530 --> 00:34:54,710
Someone that I like. We said we
would go grocery shopping together.

384
00:34:54,710 --> 00:34:56,880
Oh, that's right. Did you wait for long?

385
00:34:56,880 --> 00:35:00,110
That's okay. This is the only
appointment I have today.

386
00:35:15,490 --> 00:35:19,060
I can't tell her to stay home all day long.

387
00:35:19,060 --> 00:35:22,870
Trail her well, without being caught.

388
00:35:22,870 --> 00:35:26,540
You! Don't let your ears turn red!

389
00:35:35,010 --> 00:35:38,820
When the stem is dried out like
this, it's not fresh.

390
00:35:38,820 --> 00:35:43,360
For fish, the gills need to be a
light pink color for it to be fresh.

391
00:35:43,360 --> 00:35:45,260
These are not that fresh.

392
00:35:45,260 --> 00:35:47,760
But it's not bad for buying it at the market.

393
00:35:47,760 --> 00:35:50,230
I've never had fresh ones since I got here.

394
00:35:50,230 --> 00:35:55,430
Where you are from must have a lot of
good fish. Did you live near the ocean?

395
00:35:55,430 --> 00:35:56,970
Something like that.

396
00:35:56,970 --> 00:35:58,840
You must miss it.

397
00:35:58,840 --> 00:36:01,340
But there are a lot of good food here, so it's okay.

398
00:36:01,340 --> 00:36:03,440
Should we have some ice
cream before heading back?

399
00:36:03,440 --> 00:36:07,780
Yes, I was feeling really depressed,
but I feel better now that I met you.

400
00:36:07,780 --> 00:36:09,410
Thanks!

401
00:36:21,330 --> 00:36:22,660
What is this?

402
00:36:22,660 --> 00:36:26,260
She said she has someone to meet.
Who's this ajumma?

403
00:36:38,880 --> 00:36:42,550
She gets around and makes friends easily!

404
00:36:42,550 --> 00:36:47,450
Here's the Ma Dae Young's
psychological medical treatment report.

405
00:36:49,150 --> 00:36:53,030
Have you by any chance heard
of a woman named Kang Ji Yeon?

406
00:36:53,030 --> 00:36:55,630
Kang Ji Yeon?

407
00:36:55,630 --> 00:36:57,630
No. Why?

408
00:36:57,630 --> 00:37:01,030
She is the only woman that's involved
with Ma Dae Young, but I can't find her.

409
00:37:01,030 --> 00:37:03,940
Her resident registration got
cancelled due to unknown residency.

410
00:37:03,940 --> 00:37:07,040
We are suspecting that they
had a child between them.

411
00:37:07,040 --> 00:37:13,550
Then, they could still be helping him to run
away, whether it's the woman or the child.

412
00:37:13,550 --> 00:37:15,080
That's possible.

413
00:37:15,080 --> 00:37:16,880
Hand me that information, too.

414
00:37:16,880 --> 00:37:21,290
Nam Do Hyung finds people
better than a typical cop.

415
00:37:21,290 --> 00:37:23,620
Ah, geez!

416
00:37:25,160 --> 00:37:28,790
How did I get entangled with this conman?

417
00:37:30,130 --> 00:37:34,200
I will take responsibility,
so turn the boat.

418
00:37:38,670 --> 00:37:43,110
Our Police Officer Hong is a much
nicer person that you'd expect.

419
00:37:43,110 --> 00:37:47,650
This guy! Are you crazy?! Do I look like your friend?

420
00:37:52,480 --> 00:37:54,620
Jin Gyeong Won

421
00:37:54,620 --> 00:37:56,190
Jin Gyeong Won?

422
00:37:56,190 --> 00:37:58,090
Do you know him?

423
00:37:58,090 --> 00:38:04,230
Since 2009, he treated Ma Dae Young
most frequently every few months.

424
00:38:05,700 --> 00:38:08,370
Jin Gyeong Won

425
00:38:09,530 --> 00:38:12,700
Yes, he was my patient.

426
00:38:12,700 --> 00:38:15,410
You know Ma Dae Young, Doctor?

427
00:38:15,410 --> 00:38:18,980
Yes. He came occasionally and got treated.

428
00:38:18,980 --> 00:38:24,150
He was suffering from anger control
disorder and extreme manic depression.

429
00:38:25,020 --> 00:38:27,750
Has he come recently?

430
00:38:33,860 --> 00:38:35,330
No.

431
00:38:36,260 --> 00:38:38,500
He hasn't come lately.

432
00:38:50,310 --> 00:38:51,680
It's here.

433
00:38:51,680 --> 00:38:54,380
- Oh, you work here?- Yes.

434
00:38:54,380 --> 00:38:57,150
This is Cha Si Ah's house?

435
00:38:58,080 --> 00:39:00,890
You should have double
checked everything before!

436
00:39:00,890 --> 00:39:02,450
What's this?! We almost got in big trouble!

437
00:39:02,450 --> 00:39:05,260
We almost got caught!

438
00:39:05,260 --> 00:39:07,890
They were like that because
it was Cha Si Ah's house.

439
00:39:07,890 --> 00:39:10,160
Hmm? What was?

440
00:39:10,160 --> 00:39:12,030
It's nothing. Here you go.

441
00:39:12,030 --> 00:39:13,430
Bye then.

442
00:39:13,430 --> 00:39:15,330
Bye.

443
00:39:26,680 --> 00:39:28,750
Noona, that's not it.

444
00:39:28,750 --> 00:39:30,820
What's not it?

445
00:39:30,820 --> 00:39:34,450
Whatever you think, that's not it.

446
00:39:35,390 --> 00:39:37,190
Where are you going?

447
00:39:39,220 --> 00:39:44,300
You really have a serious symptom! What will
you do with the picture of my house door?

448
00:39:44,400 --> 00:39:48,100
- Do you want to feel my presence
even to that extent? - I'm going nuts.

449
00:39:48,200 --> 00:39:50,140
I'm going nuts, too!

450
00:39:50,140 --> 00:39:53,410
My head is about to explode,
just with my own problems!

451
00:39:53,410 --> 00:39:57,380
The crucial fact is that there
is no space for you in my heart.

452
00:39:57,380 --> 00:39:59,780
It's okay not to have the space, really.

453
00:40:06,150 --> 00:40:09,790
Was I too harsh?

454
00:40:09,790 --> 00:40:13,890
Love is such a hassle.

455
00:40:19,360 --> 00:40:20,470
Heo Joon Jae?

456
00:40:20,470 --> 00:40:24,300
This is Heo Chi Hyeon. I'm near Joon Jae's house.

457
00:40:27,310 --> 00:40:31,210
Cheong. Let me hold this for you.

458
00:40:31,210 --> 00:40:33,210
Okay.

459
00:40:38,020 --> 00:40:42,120
Please go ahead and go down first. I need
to ask the professor about something else.

460
00:40:42,120 --> 00:40:45,220
Hurry up. I'm not your taxi.

461
00:40:45,220 --> 00:40:47,990
Since it's cold, blast the heater on.

462
00:40:47,990 --> 00:40:49,930
Alright.

463
00:40:52,800 --> 00:40:56,700
It's my car. I'll take care of it on my own.

464
00:41:01,910 --> 00:41:04,240
Department of Neuropsychiatry
Professor Jin Gyeong Won

465
00:41:10,880 --> 00:41:15,290
He came yesterday. Ma Dae Young.

466
00:41:15,290 --> 00:41:17,060
Why did he come?

467
00:41:17,060 --> 00:41:22,790
If he doesn't take his medication,
he can't control his violent nature.

468
00:41:22,790 --> 00:41:26,030
He is someone who killed Dam Ryeong and Se Hwa.

469
00:41:26,030 --> 00:41:28,200
He is after us even here, too.

470
00:41:28,200 --> 00:41:32,600
He also saw the end of himself yesterday,

471
00:41:33,510 --> 00:41:35,570
and said this.

472
00:41:35,570 --> 00:41:40,280
- It wasn't me. It was not me. - What?

473
00:41:43,280 --> 00:41:49,290
He didn't kill? Then who?

474
00:41:49,290 --> 00:41:53,690
He didn't tell me so I don't know, either.

475
00:41:56,500 --> 00:42:02,230
I told you that. You can't change fate that easily.

476
00:42:02,230 --> 00:42:08,540
Even now, send the person
back to where she belongs.

477
00:42:08,540 --> 00:42:10,580
Would Ma Dae Young come back here?

478
00:42:10,580 --> 00:42:13,450
I told him that I'd prepare the medicine.

479
00:42:14,180 --> 00:42:16,520
He will come soon.

480
00:42:16,520 --> 00:42:19,690
When he comes, can you contact me?

481
00:42:19,690 --> 00:42:21,520
Sure.

482
00:42:29,830 --> 00:42:32,860
I'm sorry. I lost Cheong.

483
00:42:35,730 --> 00:42:39,470
- Hurry up!  - I'm on the way.

484
00:42:39,470 --> 00:42:41,640
I just ignored the traffic light twice!

485
00:42:41,640 --> 00:42:44,100
What will happen if she goes around
alone and meets Ma Dae Young?

486
00:42:44,100 --> 00:42:45,640
You need to take full responsibility,
Officer Hong.

487
00:42:45,640 --> 00:42:48,780
Why would I take that respons—

488
00:42:52,350 --> 00:42:55,150
Ah, why is she not answering the phone?

489
00:43:27,790 --> 00:43:29,620
Thank you.

490
00:43:29,620 --> 00:43:31,390
Help yourself.

491
00:43:31,390 --> 00:43:34,190
Is it "pour-eat" or "dip-eat"?

492
00:43:34,190 --> 00:43:37,230
I'm talking about the sauce. Do I pour it or dip it?

493
00:43:37,230 --> 00:43:43,470
Ah. "Pour-eat, dip-eat." As for me, "dip-eat."

494
00:43:43,470 --> 00:43:49,110
I'm glad. I also prefer dip-eat, but since Heo Joon
